 1 //! `ciabatta ai` — an AI assistant that learns your codebase.
 2 //!
 3 //! The assistant is a small daemon plus two front ends:
 4 //!
 5 //!   * an HTTP server (the "AI assistant" daemon) that renders the live
 6 //!     architecture mind map in the browser and exposes a JSON API
 7 //!   * a Ratatui chat TUI (the default way to talk to it)
 8 //!   * `ciabatta ai ask "..."` for one-shot questions from the shell
 9 //!
10 //! As it works, the assistant tags files with architecture labels (pending
11 //! your confirmation), builds a file→architecture map whose path scores grow
12 //! with use, and keeps a 1–100 confidence score trained by your feedback —
13 //! low scores behave like a junior dev, high scores like a senior dev. All of
14 //! that state lives in `.ciabatta/ai/brain.json`.
