 4 //! The command runs through the shell (so pipes / `&&` / redirects work). Its
 5 //! stdout and stderr are captured line-by-line into a bounded ring buffer, and a
 6 //! tiny web server (see [`server`]) serves a single-page UI that polls for new
 7 //! lines, searches the whole buffer, lets you bookmark ("point at") lines, and
 8 //! fires notifications when a line matches a trigger phrase.
 9 //!
10 //! Bookmarks and triggers **persist to disk** under `~/.ciabatta/watch/`, keyed
11 //! by the command string, so they survive restarts. Log lines themselves are
